resources.string: The PlayStation 4 (PS4) is a home video game console developed by Sony Interactive Entertainment. Announced as the successor to the PlayStation 3 in February 2013, it was launched on November 15, 2013, in North America, November 29, 2013, in Europe, South America and Australia, and on February 22, 2014, in Japan.

APU Developed by AMD in cooperation with Sony\nCPU consist of two 28 nm quad-core Jaguar modules totaling 8 64-bit x86-64 cores\nGPU consist of 18 compute units to produce a theoretical peak performance of 1.84 TFLOPS
Orbit OS\nBased upon a customized FreeBSD
Support HDR, Wifi and Ethernet conectivity, and two 3.0 ports.
